<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-26T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-26T13:00:00-05:00" n="638" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5431/256: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-26T13:00:00-05:00">October 26, 1935—1
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>67. Your 43, October 26, 11 a.m. Reworded proposals together with
                                added concessions have distinctly bettered American offers on
                                watches. Nef has probably reassured Stucki on this point. Swiss
                                watch specialist, who left yesterday on the <hi rend="italic">Bremen</hi>, declared he would explain the nature and value of
                                our concessions to Swiss industry.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>